-- Chinese State Councilor Dai Bingguo to Visit North Korea Today, Kyodo Says
-- B y   T a k   K u m a k u r a
-- 2010-11-30T22:22:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-30/china-s-dai-will-urge-north-korea-to-join-six-party-talks-kyodo-reports.html
Chinese State Councilor Dai Bingguo
will visit North Korea as early as today to ease tensions in the
region, Kyodo News reported from Beijing, citing unidentified
officials.  Dai will urge the communist country to send a
representative to six-nation talks, the report said. Tensions
heightened after North Korea fired artillery at a South Korean
island last month.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Takehiko Kumakura at 
 tkumakura@bloomberg.net  